  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Yields in Sri Lanka\u2019s govt securities fall after President Gotabaya resigns",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s bond and Treasury bill rates closed lower at the secondary market trade on Friday while a guidance peg on interbank spot trading strengthened, dealers said.",
        "The move comes after Goatabaya Rajapaksa resigned from his post after fleeing the country.",
        "A bond maturing on 01.06.25 closed at 27.00/28.00 percent down from 28.00/25 percent on Thursday close.",
        "A bond maturing on 15.07.29 closed at 28.00/29.00 percent steady from 29.00/30 percent in the previous close.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions strengthened by 66 cents to 361.24 against the US dollar on July 15 from the previous 361.90, data showed on Friday.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.24 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 15, steady from Thursday, online data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.24 -359.00 rupees, also steady from the previous day. (Colombo/July 15/2022)"
      ],
